This paper deals with deep learning and medical imaging, which are both topics that fall under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) also suggests that the paper could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with medical data, which could also place it under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the proposed General-to-detailed GAN (GDGAN) is a novel architecture that combines two GANs, which could also place the paper under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
